1. *Vlasnik* je obavestio radnike o novim pravilima. (The *owner* informed the workers about the new rules.)
2. Radnici su se žalili na ponašanje *vlasnika* prema njima. (The workers complained about the behavior of the *owner* towards them.)
3. Prema zakonu, *vlasnik* je odgovoran za sve nezgode koje se dogode na njegovom posedu. (According to the law, the *owner* is responsible for all accidents that happen on his property.)
4. Stanari su se okupili da bi razgovarali sa *vlasnikom* zgrade. (The tenants gathered to talk to the *owner* of the building.)
5. Kada je prodavac pozvao *vlasnika* da potpiše ugovor, on nije bio dostupan. (When the seller called the *owner* to sign the contract, he was not available.)
6. *Vlasniku* su dodeljene nagrade za poslovni uspeh. (The *owner* was awarded prizes for business success.)
7. Policija je uhapsila *vlasnika* zbog sumnje u kršenje zakona. (The police arrested the *owner* on suspicion of breaking the law.)
8. *Vlasnika* kuće nisu uspeli da pronađu nakon požara. (They couldn't find the *owner* of the house after the fire.)
9. Iako je *vlasnik* restorana obećao da će popraviti kvarove, to još uvek nije učinio. (Although the *owner* of the restaurant promised to fix the malfunctions, he still hasn't done so.)
10. Kupac je pitao *vlasnika* da li je cena nekretnine pregovariva. (The buyer asked the *owner* if the price of the property was negotiable.)